---
import '../../styles/global.css';

const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Tabi Travel App" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - Tabi</title>
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-900 font-mono">
  <div class="min-h-screen max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-12">
      <nav class="mb-8">
        <a href="/projects/tabi" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm">← Back to Tabi</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Privacy Policy - Tabi</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="space-y-8">
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> Aug 4, 2025<br><strong>Last Updated:</strong> Aug 4, 2025</p>
      
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Our Privacy Commitment</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Tabi is built with privacy as our foundation. We believe your location data is personal and should remain under your complete control. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Location Data</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• <strong>What:</strong> Tabi accesses your device's location services to track your travels</li>
          <li>• <strong>How:</strong> Location data is collected automatically in the background at periodic intervals</li>
          <li>• <strong>Where Stored:</strong> All location data is stored locally on your device only</li>
          <li>• <strong>Never Shared:</strong> Your raw location data never leaves your device</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Reverse Geocoding Data</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          <li>• <strong>What:</strong> We use Apple's reverse geocoding service to convert coordinates into readable city and country names</li>
          <li>• <strong>How:</strong> Your device sends coordinates to Apple's servers and receives location names in return</li>
          <li>• <strong>Apple's Role:</strong> This process is handled by Apple according to their privacy policy</li>
          <li>• <strong>Our Access:</strong> We only receive the city/country names, not your raw coordinates</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Information We Do NOT Store or Have Access To</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We do not store or have access to:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          <li>• Your personal identity or contact information</li>
          <li>• Your raw GPS coordinates or precise locations</li>
          <li>• Your travel patterns or behavior data</li>
          <li>• Any data that could identify you personally</li>
          <li>• Analytics about your app usage</li>
          <li>• Advertising identifiers or tracking data</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>We do not share your data. Period.</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          <li>• No advertising networks</li>
          <li>• No data brokers or marketing companies</li>
          <li>• No business partners or affiliates</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Data Storage and Security</h2>
        
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Local Storage</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• All your travel data is stored locally on your device using iOS secure storage</li>
          <li>• Data is protected by your device's security features (passcode, Face ID, Touch ID)</li>
          <li>• We cannot access your data remotely</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">No Cloud Storage</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• We do not maintain servers with your personal data</li>
          <li>• We do not backup your data to any cloud service</li>
          <li>• Your data travels with your device only</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Data Retention</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          <li>• Data remains on your device until you delete the app or manually clear it</li>
          <li>• You have complete control over data retention periods</li>
          <li>• No data is retained on our end when you delete the app</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Your Rights and Controls</h2>
        
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Complete Control</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• <strong>Access:</strong> View all your data within the app</li>
          <li>• <strong>Export:</strong> Export your data in various formats anytime</li>
          <li>• <strong>Delete:</strong> Remove all data by deleting the app or using in-app clearing options</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Location Permissions</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm">
          <li>• You can revoke location permissions at any time in iOS Settings</li>
          <li>• The app will stop collecting new location data immediately</li>
          <li>• Previously collected data remains on your device until you delete it</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Tabi does not knowingly collect information from children under 13. Since all data remains on the device, we have no way to determine user age. Parents should supervise children's use of location-tracking apps.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. We will notify users of significant changes through:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>• App Store update notes</li>
          <li>• Updated policy posted on our website</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your information, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong>Email:</strong> help@meiwin.helpscoutapp.com<br>
          <strong>Website:</strong> https://meiwin.github.io/projects/tabi
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Since we don't collect personal data, we may not be able to identify specific user accounts, but we're happy to address general privacy questions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">International Users</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Tabi works globally, and all data processing occurs locally on your device regardless of your location. No data crosses international borders through our services.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <p class="text-center text-gray-400 mt-4">
        © {currentYear} /meiwin/. All rights reserved
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>